Title: UAC Care System Operations Dashboard

Introduction:
The modern public service and healthcare ecosystem generates large volumes of operational data across multiple touchpoints, such as case intake, transfers, 
and discharges. Decision-mak-ers often struggle to convert this raw data into timely, actionable insights, especially when teams 
rely on static spreadsheets or delayed reports. Interactive dashboards and analytical tools have therefore become essential for monitoring system 
load, understanding backlogs, and plan-ning resources more effectively.
This project presents the development of an operations command center dashboard, built using Python and Streamlit, to visualize key indicators 
related to the UAC (Unaccompanied Alien Children) care system. The dashboard consolidates daily and monthly metrics from a SQLite database and 
presents them via intuitive views, including Executive Summary, Opera-tions Monitor, Backlog & Risk, and Scenario Lab. By providing a single, integrated interface, 
the application helps users track total system load, intake pressure, discharges, and scenario-based projections.
From a management perspective, the dashboard demonstrates how data-driven tools can im-prove situational awareness, support proactive decision-making, 
and enhance accountability. It bridges the gap between operational data and strategic planning by transforming complex ta-bles into clear visual stories 
that can be understood by both technical and non-technical stake-holders. The project shows how lightweight technologies like Streamlit and SQLite can be combined 
to deliver a practical decision-support solution.

